doctype html
html(lang="en")
    head
        title='Why do I keep a diary?: The Portfolio of Sophie Thomas'
        include ../_includes/head.jade
        meta(name='twitter:description', content='Firstly, yes I keep a diary but not in the way you may think. I don’t sit there writing ‘Dear Diary’ with paragraphs of what I did that day. Instead every night before bed I jot down the tasks I did that day which consists of a small, usually rubbish, illustration and a sentence of what I did. An example would be an illustration of a shopping trolley with the sentence of ‘Went shopping to get a few frozen items.’ I know, such an awful example… but it was the first thing that popped into my head when writing this.')
        link(rel='stylesheet', href='../assets/css/main.css', type='text/css')
        meta(name='twitter:image', content='http://sophiethomas.co.uk/assets/images/author.jpg')

    body
    
        div.siteBorders
        
        div#container
        
            include ../_includes/header.jade

            div#articleList.col-12
                div.line: h1 Why do I keep a diary?
                p.date: em Published: 22nd April 2016
                
                div.articleContent
                    p Firstly, yes I keep a diary but not in the way you may think. I don’t sit there writing ‘Dear Diary’ with paragraphs of what I did that day. Instead every night before bed I jot down the tasks I did that day which consists of a small, usually rubbish, illustration and a sentence of what I did. An example would be an illustration of a shopping trolley with the sentence of ‘Went shopping to get a few frozen items.’ I know, such an awful example… but it was the first thing that popped into my head when writing this.
                    p Why do I do this every evening before bed?
                    p I personally feel that it is a great way to reflect on what I’ve actually done that day as it is very easy to forget the small tasks that you do. By writing the things I have done down on paper I can truly see what I have achieved that day allowing me to access whether I have done a lot of work or not. In addition to this, I can also make notes on how I felt about some of those tasks without writing an essay. It is also quite funny to look back at what I wrote and did. It always make me laugh!
                    img(src="../assets/images/articles/2016/diary-2016.jpeg" alt="Diary Snippet" class="post-img")
                    p I have only been keeping a diary for a few months now and I feel it’s a brilliant thing to do. This is mainly due to it not taking a long time to do as it is only a quick illustration and a short sentence of what I did and it allows me to see what I have achieved that day.
                    br
                    br
                    p Do you keep a diary? If you do, do you feel it benefits you?
                        
